    • loadPathGroup

      public static List<PathPlannerTrajectory> loadPathGroup(String name, boolean reversed, PathConstraints constraint, PathConstraints... constraints)
      Load a path file from storage as a path group. This will separate the path into multiple paths based on the waypoints marked as "stop points"
      Parameters:
      name - The name of the path group to load
      reversed - Should the robot follow this path group reversed
      constraint - The PathConstraints (max velocity, max acceleration) of the first path in the group
      constraints - The PathConstraints (max velocity, max acceleration) of the remaining paths in the group. If there are less constraints than paths, the last constrain given will be used for the remaining paths.
      Returns:
      A List of all generated paths in the group

    • loadPathGroup

      public static List<PathPlannerTrajectory> loadPathGroup(String name, PathConstraints constraint, PathConstraints... constraints)
      Load a path file from storage as a path group. This will separate the path into multiple paths based on the waypoints marked as "stop points"
      Parameters:
      name - The name of the path group to load
      constraint - The PathConstraints (max velocity, max acceleration) of the first path in the group
      constraints - The PathConstraints (max velocity, max acceleration) of the remaining paths in the group. If there are less constraints than paths, the last constrain given will be used for the remaining paths.
      Returns:
      A List of all generated paths in the group

    • generatePath

      public static PathPlannerTrajectory generatePath(PathConstraints constraints, boolean reversed, List<PathPoint> points)
      Generate a path on-the-fly from a list of points As you can't see the path in the GUI when using this method, make sure you have a good idea of what works well and what doesn't before you use this method in competition. Points positioned in weird configurations such as being too close together can lead to really janky paths.
      Parameters:
      constraints - The max velocity and max acceleration of the path
      reversed - Should the robot follow this path reversed
      points - Points in the path
      Returns:
      The generated path

    • getConstraintsFromPath

      public static PathConstraints getConstraintsFromPath(String name)
      Load path constraints from a path file in storage. This can be used to change path max vel/accel in the GUI instead of updating and rebuilding code. This requires that max velocity and max acceleration have been explicitly set in the GUI.
      Parameters:
      name - The name of the path to load constraints from
      Returns:
      The constraints from the path file, null if they are not present in the file
